{{see|bo}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Of Scandinavian origin. Old Norse bua = 'to build, to live, to dwell'; Swedish bo = 'dweller' cf. Stockholmbo = 'dweller in Stockholm'.
This name could also be a variant writing of the given name Beau. The name Beau comes from the French word beau = 'beautiful'.

====Proper Noun====
'''Bo'''

# A male first name.

